Female genitalia. Segment IX (IX) rectangular in lateral aspect, mostly sclerotized but membranous posterodorsally and bearing 1 to 3 setae on each anterodorsal side, with long apodemal extension on each anteroventral corner. Segment X (X) (segment XI of
Schmid 1969
) membranous dorsally, with pair of setose longitudinal sclerites dorsolaterally; ventral setose area weakly sclerotized, but membranous apicomesally; with pair of setose distal lobes, each bearing cercus. Vulvar scale (vs) large, each side sclerotized, thumb-like in lateral aspect, with long stout setae apicolaterally; posterolateral margins round in ventral aspect, semimembranous mesally, projecting slightly beyond lateral corners. Vaginal chamber (vc) sclerotized, expanded anterad and dorsad in lateral aspect; ventral part wide, vase-shaped in ventral view.
